    "content": "<h1>SISTRUM</h1><p>An ancient percussion instrument. A sistrum had a thin metal frame with many metal rods or loops that made jingling sounds when shaken. In <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam6:5\">2&nbsp;Samuel 6:5</a>, this instrument is translated as &quot;castanets&quot; in the New Living Translation.</p><p><em>See</em> <span data-bnType=\"resourceReference\" data-resourceId=\"6414\" data-resourceType=\"TyndaleBibleDictionary\">Musical Instruments (Mena anim; Shalishim)</span>.</p>",
